{
  "texts": [
    "Technology advancements like the introduction of the internet and social media have increased the availability of big data (Murshed et al. 2023).",
    "A prominent task to uncover hidden topics from big data is \"topic modelling\".",
    "Topic modelling (TM) is a type of statistical learning approach for detecting coherent topics in a document (Blei et al. 2003; Ogunleye et al. 2023).",
    "The idea of TM spanned from the early algorithms namely, latent semantic analy-sis (Deerwester et al. 1990) and probabilistic latent semantic analysis (Hofmann 1999).",
    "The latter approach was criticised for the inability to account for generative probabilistic models of the documents which led to the development of latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA) by Blei et al. (2003)."
  ]
}